(Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Outgoing United States President Barack Obama has extended sanctions against Zimbabwe by at least another year, a report says.News24 CorrespondentHarare - Some boarding schools in Zimbabwe have banned their pupils from bringing breakfast cereal with them because the students have been using it to brew beer, it was reported on Tuesday.Zimbabwean school pupils headed back for the start of a new term&nbsp;on Tuesday, minus, or so the authorities hoped, their porridge.The Chronicle&nbsp;newspaper said at least three well-known schools in the south of the country had warned parents that oats and cereal made of sorghum would be confiscated.&nbsp;That's because pupils are apparently mixing the cereals with brown sugar and yeast and then leaving it to ferment in the sun, says the paper, which is published in Bulawayo.Chemist Michael Dube told the Chronicle that the illicit brew can have "devastating effects" on pupils' health.The Zimbabwe authorities are becoming increasingly worried about illicit alcohol consumption among school pupils.Last month police in Bulawayo arrested 224 pupils attending a "vuzu" party, at which alcohol is consumed on the outskirts of the city, according to a report carried by&nbsp;Nehanda Radio.Some of the students were as young as 13.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.